NT||cp|8|AT|^B@2
^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Suppose Ann leads a low heart. Normally Kim would play low. However, since Ann is forced to play her singleton K, in this rare case it is ok to play high--play the Ace. Because unlike normal second hand low, in this case Kim's Ace is capturing Ann's @HK--second hand high still captures an opponents honor.|
PG| ***** 52 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|^B@2
^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|There was a similar idea when Ann played the @DQ. It was right for Kim to play high. Because again, Kim is capturing one of Ann's honors. In fact, had Kim plays low, then Ann will score 2 diamond tricks (the Queen and King) instead of the 1 she is entitled to.|
