^-|CP||FP||at|^B@2^Z@3Bridge information stays with me as long as writing on the sand at the beach. It takes only one soft wave to wash everything away. However, as I get older I become more persistent and keep writing on the sand--reviewing the material over and over. This week I have an interesting read on "Double Dummy" playing problems. It is part of chapter IX, Part II of ^*IThe Play of the Hand at Bridge^*N by Louis H. Watson. |
